BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:MggI67TkBKvzHjd9MDBpm
SUMMARY:Living Voices: Winning Her Wings
DTSTAMP:20260328T110742Z
DTSTART:20260402T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:They flew planes. They fought prejudice. They made history. Win
	ning Her Wings brings to life the groundbreaking Women Airforce Service Pi
	lots (WASPs). Follow journeys of women who faced and broke barriers togeth
	er\\\, fighting for justice in a time of global conflict and domestic prej
	udice. Discover how they soared—despite the odds. \\nThis new multimedia p
	erformance by Living Voices blends live theatre and archival film to honor
	 the women who served with courage. Premiering in 2026 for Women’s History
	 Month. This event takes place during our Free First Thursday hours. Seats
	 are first come first served. \\nLiving Voices combines live theatrical pe
	rformances with archival film\\\, turning history into a moving personal j
	ourney. This performance will take place in the Joshua Green Foundation Th
	eater on MOHAI’s second floor.\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/living-voices-wi
	nning-her-wings/2026-04-02/1/\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/living-voices-winning-her-wings/2026-04-02/1/
LOCATION:Joshua Green Foundation Theater\\\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seat
	tle\\\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
